    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, you're saying it's unnecessary to take it offline? The automated scanner specifically flagged this as a \"Critical\" severity because it's an unauthenticated remote code execution vector. If an attacker hits this, they have full database access. How can you call it a \"quick patch\" risk when the scan says it's a high-probability exploit? Are you sure you aren't underestimating the actual exposure here?",
